  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Resilience Support to Sustain Livelihoods of South Sudanese Refugees in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to improve the income, self-reliance and livelihoods of 5,682 South Sudanese refugees and their host communities in and around Palabek refugee settlement in northern Uganda. The project will address crop production constraints for refugees in order to increase food availability in the targeted zones and in the neighboring communities, provide agricultural inputs; improve agricultural practices; and provide LWR&apos;s Material Resources for immediate relief for women and children. The project will be implemented by LWR in partnership with African Women and Youth Action for Development.</narrative>
  </description>
